            <title>[THRIFT-3564] C++/Qt: potential core dump in TQTcpServer in case an exception occurs in TAsyncProcessor::process()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3564</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s undefined behaviour, if a Qt object (sender) get&apos;s deleted while executing on of it&apos;s slots. This can happen in case an exception occurs in TQTcpServer::beginDecode() as the call to ctxMap_.erase() will delete the sender of the Qt signal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
