                            <comment id="15104935" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jan 2016 08:35:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user szenker opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/802&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/802&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3564&quot; title=&quot;C++/Qt: potential core dump in TQTcpServer in case an exception occurs in TAsyncProcessor::process()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3564&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3564&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: potential core dump in TQTcpServer&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    TQTcpServer: it&apos;s not allowed to delete the sender of a Qt signal (QTcpSocket) while executing one of its slots. This could happen in TQTcpServer::beginDecode() in case an exception occurred. Ensured, that deletion is deferred in all cases.&lt;/p&gt;

